Riders in the Sky
comments: Parody version. Vocal refrain by I.W. Harper, Sir Frederick Gas, and the Sons of the Sons of the Backwoodsmen. There are two versions of this song. The original version ended with "I can do without his singing, but I wish I had is dough!" after "All we ever hear is 'Ghost Riders' sung by Vaughn Monroe". This supposedly outraged Monroe, and RCA-Victor quickly withdrew the record and replaced it with one that had a different ending (without Spike's knowledge or permission). Some copies with the original ending did manage to get out and this version is considered highly collectible.
